videoSnippet.title: Wizard Jobava Baadur vs The Gentleman Nigel Short
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator Baadur Jobava vs Nigel Short
Xtracon Chess Open (2017), Elsinore, rd 8, Jul-28 
English Opening: Agincourt Defense. Neo Catalan Declined (A14)

1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. Nf3 Be7 5. O-O O-O 6. Qc2 b6 7. cd5 Nd5 8. Nc3 c6 9. Rd1 Bb7 10. d4 Nd7 11. e4 Nc3 12. bc3 Qc7 13. Bf4 Bd6 14. e5 Be7 15. h4 Rfe8 16. h5 b5 17. h6 g6 18. Nh2 Nb6 19. Ng4 c5 20. Nf6 Bf6 21. ef6 Qc8 22. Bb7 Qb7 23. dc5 Nc4 24. Bd6 Qf3 25. a4 ba4 26. Rd4 Na5 27. Rf4 Qb7 28. Rb4 Qd7 29. Qa4 Nc6 30. Rab1 Rec8 31. Rb7 Qe8 32. f4 Kh8 33. Qe4 Kg8 34. Qa4 e5 35. fe5 Qe6 36. Qb3 Qb3 37. R1b3 Na5 38. e6 Nb3 39. ef7 Kh8 40. Re7 Nd2 41. Re8 Re8 42. fe8Q Re8 43. f7 Re1 44. Kg2 Re2 45. Kh3 Rf2 46. Be5 Rf6 47. Bf6#

GM Baadur Jobava's tournament win at the 2017 Xtracon Open was only partly Shakespearean. It was played in Elsinore, Denmark, home of "Hamlet." But it was far from a tragedy. Instead, Jobava produced a few moves almost as memorable as that quotable play.
